The paper introduces a learning-based algorithm for low-rank decomposition, which involves optimization and approximation techniques. This suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of sketching matrices and singular value decomposition may indicate that the paper could also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the mention of experiments with different types of data sets and mixed matrices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
